  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Safe Water for Indigenous Schools &amp; Villages</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">We provide safe water for indigenous schools having to use polluted streams or contaminated wells.
Why should children be sick and drop out of school from bad water where it often rains?  
Principals report absenteeism from sickness drops from as much as 50% to less than 10% 
after our rain-catchment  tanks are installed. We work among the indigenous Guaymi people of Panama&apos;s islands and mainland.</narrative>
  </description>
